The UIF says it has R30 billion available in immediately accessible funds tragetting formal employees who have lost income as a result of the lockdown. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Unemployment Insurance Fund says it has R30 billion set aside for formal employees who have lost income over the lockdown period. Robert Legh from Business SA says employees have started to apply. READ: Coronavirus threatens nearly 20 million African jobs: study Employees can apply for relief from R 3,500 up to R6,700 a month. "We are assured by the UIF that they are ready to start processing claims," Legh said. "The reality is that as of yesterday, some 10,000 claims had already been made." - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.